{
  "name": "RPlog_Coffee_and_Hydrospanners",
  "title": "Coffee and Hydrospanners",
  "summary": "On the Ord Mantell tarmac during a quiet morning inspection, Ghost Squadron pilot 2nd Lieutenant Raxis L'ygr meets the new Bothan mechanic Askra Sho'bre, a cybernetic-armed survivor of Nar Shaddaa, and her foul-mouthed astromech Tinker. Over coffee, the two strike up an easy, sprawling conversation, swapping stories about droids, the Empire, the Jedi Temple, swoop racing, and Boba Fett while Askra clambers over Raxis's X-wing, Ghost 3, realigning its laser cannons and digging old TIE shrapnel from the hull. She slowly recalls fragments of her past, an Alderaanian clan, a robed, limping foster father with a Nexu and a silver object on his belt, that hint at a possible Force-sensitive lineage, and Raxis gently urges her to visit the Temple. As they trade flirtation, squadron gossip, and war stories, Raxis's pager calls him to scramble, sending him sprinting for his flight suit.",
